data.title: Iraq takes another step down a long, hard road
data.meta_description: Votes were being counted on Friday after an encouraging turnout in the previous day's election in Iraq. The poll was free of large-scale violence and saw wide participation by Sunnis. But it will be hard to construct a government that all can accept, and harder still to defeat the insurgency and turn Iraq into something approaching a normal country | News
data.text:
Votes were being counted on Friday after an encouraging turnout in the previous day's election in Iraq. The poll was free of large-scale violence and saw wide participation by Sunnis. But it will be hard to construct a government that all can accept, and harder still to defeat the insurgency and turn Iraq into something approaching a normal country

Dec 19th 2005|
